(
<figureCitation id="13742A33B249FF969E62F925FB61F8B5" box="[1072,1196,1780,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="19.[131,142,1265,1283]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1205]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[132,1455,216,1205]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIG. 12. — A-E, Epitonium polacia (Dall, 1889): A, shell from DW130 (4.9 mm height); new to the eastern Atlantic; B, protoconch of the same shell; C, scanning electron micrograph of the same protoconch; D, E, shell from DW130 (4.3 mm height); F, G, Opaliopsis opalina (Dall, 1927): F, shell from DW130 (5.9 mm height); new to the eastern Atlantic; G, protoconch of the same shell; H-K, Epitonium nanum (Jeffreys, 1884), shell from DW130 (2.9 mm height); new to Spanish waters; I, Narrimania concinna (Sykes, 1925), shell from DW130 (4.6 mm height); new to Spanish waters; J, protoconch of the same specimen; K, scanning electron micrograph of the protoconch of a juvenile, live taken specimen, same locality; the arrow points to the protoconch-teleoconch limit. Scale bars: 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726052/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="528">
Fig. 12 
